<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861201-0099 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell UnitGets Army WorkFor $804.9 Million</HL><DD> 12/01/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD GE BA CAT ML WX RTN FMC MRNAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Helicopter Co., a division of McDonnell Douglas Corp., received an $804.9 million addition to an Army contract for AH-64A advanced attack helicopters.    General Electric Co. won contracts totaling $197.3 million for Army helicopter engines and Navy nuclear-propulsion parts.    Boeing Co. was awarded $59.7 million in Air Force contracts for aircraft equipment.    Caterpillar Tractor Co. was issued a $41.3 million addition to an Army contract for diesel tractor engines.    American Systems Corp. got a $39.1 million Navy contract for engineering and technical services.    Martin Marietta Ordnance Systems Inc., a unit of Martin Marietta Corp., was given a $23.4 million addition to an Army contract for operating the Milan ammunition plant in Milan, Tenn.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. received a $21 million addition to a Navy contract for nuclear-propulsion components.    Raytheon Co. won $20.8 million in contracts for Navy missile parts and for Army missile repair kits.    Space Communications Co. was awarded an $18 million addition to an Air Force contract for space operations support.    A joint venture of Holmes andamp; Narver and Morrison-Knudson Corp. received a $13.4 million addition to an Army contract for base support services at Redstone Arsenal in Alabama.    FMC Corp. was given a $12.7 million addition to an Army contract for armored vehicles.    Freightliner Corp. got a $12.1 million addition to an Army contract for tractor parts. </TEXT></DOC>